<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-887-884  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 887 884.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Modern Office Technology  Nov 1989 v34 n11 p108(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>An industry is born. (Information andamp; Image Management)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Bogue, David T.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The success of the Association for Information and ImageManagement (AIIM) Show and Conference in San Francisco in Jun 1989led attendees to note that the meeting may have marked the birthof an industry.andP;  The feeling was due in some part to therecognition that those working in the field have finally realizedamong corporate managers.andP;  Organizations now consider informationand image management, as well as the related fields of transactionprocessing, technical drawing management, electronic publishingand archiving and storage, one of the strategic elements in theirinformation strategies.andP;  Technological advances allow paper, theweak link in current information schemes, to be replaced withmagnetic and optical storage media.andP;  The changes expected as aresult of the introduction of new technologies and the outlook forthe market are discussed.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Information Resource ManagementImage ProcessingIndustry AnalysisForecastingConferencesProfessional AssociationsInformation Storage and RetrievalTechnologyOutlookAssociation for Information and Image Management.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>